      <div id="about-the-sunglasses">
      <h2>What are Westward Leaning sunglasses made from?</h2>
      <p>Westward Leaning frames are made from thick sheets of acetate, giving our sunglasses an incredibly substantial feel.</p>
      <p>All of our models use CR-39 plastic lenses, the best lenses in the world.</p>
      <p>Additionally, all of our sunglasses feature Westward Leaning’s signature piece: a unique material embedded into their temples. These materials range from California redwood and aluminum to created coral and blue sea glass.</p>
      
      <h2>Where are Westward Leaning sunglasses made?</h2>
      <p>Our sunglasses are all made by hand in Japan and San Francisco. A team of professional artisans works in our San Francisco offices to integrate neon lenses and all of the unique materials into the frames by hand.</p>
      
      <h2>How can I improve the fit of my sunglasses?</h2>
      <p>Acetate, the material used to craft our frames, is flexible. Gently bend the end of the stems inwards or outwards for a tighter or looser fit as needed.</p>
      {{ 'fit1.png' | asset_url | img_tag: 'Fit Diagram #1', 'fit-diagram' }}
      <p>You can increase the malleability of the frame by heating your sunglasses with a hairdryer. Should you choose to do so, make sure to direct the heat at the end of the stems while avoiding the unique material inlay.</p>
      {{ 'fit2.png' | asset_url | img_tag: 'Fit Diagram #2', 'fit-diagram' }}
      
      <h2>How can I best care for my Westward Leaning sunglasses?</h2>
      <p>We are proud to offer sunglasses made with the best materials and exceptional craftsmanship, and your satisfaction is important to us. We recommend that you store your sunglasses in the provided protective cases at all times when not in use. Rest sunglasses lens-side up to prevent scratching the lenses.</p>
      <p>Additionally, lenses should be cleaned regularly with either a lens cleaner or fresh water and a soft, clean cloth (you will receive such a cloth with your purchase).</p>
      <p>Although Westward Leaning sunglasses are waterproof, we do not recommend submerging our sunglasses in water as this can deteriorate the adhesives used to inlay unique materials. Moreover, we advise against leaving sunglasses exposed in high temperatures, such as in a car in Arizona in July, as acetate can warp.</p>
      
      <h2>What can I do if a screw falls out?</h2>
      <p>Any of your local opticians should be able to replace the screw. Or email us at help@westwardleaning.com and we’ll be happy to fix them for you.</p>
      
      <h2>Can I put prescription lenses in my Westward Leaning sunglasses? How?</h2>
      <p>Yes. Although Westward Leaning does not offer prescription lenses at this time, your optician will be able to fit our sunglasses with your prescription.</p>
      
      <h2>How do I determine which size I should order?</h2>
      <p>Westward Leaning prides itself on its universally flattering shapes: all of our frames have gone through two years of design research to make sure they truly are a great fit for everyone.</p>
      <p>Our Voyager circle model is available in a single size, measuring 48mm by 2mm by 145mm (lens width, nose bridge width and stem length). This makes it a more petite frame than our wayfarer.</p>
      <div class='faq-dimensions voyager'>{{ 'voyager_specs.jpg' | asset_url | img_tag: 'Voyager Dimensions' }}</div>
      <p>Our Classic wayfarer model is available in three sizes: the Standard, the Small and the Large. The Standard size is the optimal fit for 90% of our customers and we offer it for all our models. The Small and the Large, scaled down and up versions of our standard size, respectively, are appropriate for customers who’ve experienced problems with the fit of sunglasses in the past. We offer the Small and the Large in <a href='/products/small-large-size'>select models</a>. For the precise measurements of our sizes, please see below:</p>
      <div class='faq-dimensions'>{{ 'small_specs.jpg' | asset_url | img_tag: 'Small Wayfarer Sunglasses Dimensions' }}</div>
      <div class='faq-dimensions'>{{ 'wayfarer_specs.jpg' | asset_url | img_tag: 'Standard Wayfarer Sunglasses Dimensions' }}</div>
